# ABOUTME: Host -> cluster LoadBalancer routing table for the agenticburn.com wildcard router.
# ABOUTME: GENERATED by the provisioner per fleet; the committed copy is a documented placeholder.
#
# Format: one "<host>  http://<cluster-lb-host>" per line (whitespace-separated). The router
# proxies the matched host to that upstream. Unmatched hosts fall through to the unknown-host page.
#
# Facilitator clusters (repoint the value as Cluster-1 spares rotate; redeploy or hot-reload):
#   burn.agenticburn.com    http://<cluster-1-active-spare-lb>
#   wall.agenticburn.com    http://<cluster-2-lb>
#   haiku.agenticburn.com   http://<instructor-c3-haiku-lb>
#   sonnet.agenticburn.com  http://<instructor-c3-sonnet-lb>
#   opus.agenticburn.com    http://<instructor-c3-opus-lb>
#
# Per-attendee Cluster 3 (one line each, generated from the pool / fleet output):
#   a-001.agenticburn.com   http://<attendee-001-lb>
#   a-002.agenticburn.com   http://<attendee-002-lb>
#   ...
#
# No real LB hostnames are committed (clusters are provisioned per-event and torn down to $0).
